of goods bought for personal, family or household use, unless the seller, at
                any time before or at the conclusion of the contract, neither knew nor ought to have
                known that the goods were bought for any such use;

if a period of time is fixed by or determinable from the contract, at any time
                within that period unless circumstances indicate that the buyer is to choose a date;
                or

if the failure by the seller to perform any of his obligations under the
                contract or this Convention amounts to a fundamental breach of contract;
                or

if the failure by the buyer to perform any of his obligations under the
                contract or this Convention amounts to a fundamental breach of contract;
                or

if the impossibility of making restitution of the goods or of making
                restitution of the goods substantially in the condition in which the buyer received
                them is not due to his act or omission;
